1 olive oil
1 carrot
1 beetroot
1 packet beef mince
½ packet fine breadcrumbs
1 egg
1 packet sweet chilli sauce
1 bag parsley
1 cucumber
1 bag slaw mix
1 packet Dill & Parsley Mayonnaise
2 clove garlic
1 sachet Aussie Spice Blend

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• Cut carrot and beetroot into fries.
• Place veggie fries on a lined oven tray, drizzle with olive oil and season with salt and pepper.
• Toss to coat, spread out evenly, then bake until tender, 20-25 minutes.

• Meanwhile, finely chop garlic.
• In a large bowl, combine beef mince, Aussie spice blend, fine breadcrumbs (see ingredients), the egg, garlic and a pinch of salt and pepper.
• Using damp hands, roll heaped spoonfuls of the beef mixture into meatballs (3-4 per person), then flatten to make 2cm-thick rissoles. Transfer to a plate.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook rissoles in batches, until browned and cooked through, 3-4 minutes each side.
• Remove pan from heat, then add sweet chilli sauce and splash of water, turning rissoles to coat. Set aside.

• While the rissoles are cooking, slice cucumber into half-moons. Roughly chop parsley leaves.

• In a medium bowl combine slaw mix, dill & parsley mayonnaise, cucumber and a pinch of salt.

• Divide rainbow veggie fries, sweet chilli beef rissoles and creamy slaw between plates.
• Garnish with parsley to serve. Enjoy!